&lt;p&gt;We are expanding our regional team and looking for a driven, ambitious, and results-oriented &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager (AM)&lt;/strong&gt; to support our continued growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Manager at AvePoint, you will play a pivotal role in driving pipeline generation and market expansion. You will manage daily outbound activities, qualify marketing-generated leads from events, and engage enterprise-level prospects through structured outreach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also participate in showcasing AvePoint’s solutions through presentations, helping prospects understand how we support digital transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires someone proactive, energetic, and capable of driving new market penetration with minimal supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pipeline Development &amp;amp; Account Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute &lt;strong&gt;daily outbound prospecting&lt;/strong&gt; activities including cold calls, emails, and social outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and qualify &lt;strong&gt;marketing leads to webinars, road shows, and events&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct initial discovery conversations to understand prospect needs and challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a healthy pipeline to meet &lt;strong&gt;quarterly Qualified Pipeline Generation (QPG)&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;bookings targets&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution Knowledge &amp;amp; Presentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present AvePoint’s company profile and high-level solution overview to prospects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand customer challenges and solutions requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Articulate how AvePoint supports &lt;strong&gt;digital transformation, data governance, migration, and collaboration modernization&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand and explain key concepts related to &lt;strong&gt;SaaS, Digital Transformation, AI&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute daily/weekly activities to drive consistent results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Account Executives to support territory development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate activity and deal records in Excel or CRM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adapt quickly to new market conditions and develop new territories with minimal guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years’ experience in Account Management, Business development, or similar roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business development experience is an advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in selling enterprise solutions B2B digital transformation solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced, agile environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver value-based solution positioning and articulate ROI aligned to regulatory and business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with pre-sales, customer success, and partner teams to ensure successful solution adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify upsell and cross-sell opportunities within existing accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate pipeline forecasting and CRM reporting&lt;/li&gt;
